Mounting:Mounting refers to the initial creation and insertion of a component into the DOM. It happens only once in the component's lifecycle, when the component is first rendered and added to the DOM tree. The componentDidMount lifecycle method is called after the component is mounted.

Rendering:it can happen multiple times throughout the component's lifecycle, triggered by changes in props or state.



